snippet.textDisplay:
Video idea: (Lasik or Lasek, BTW: which one did you have?) do a video on how your eye laser treatment results; glare issues/floaters/sunlight. 
I had it done years ago, and while mostly great, I did get more issues with glare in light environments that can cause eye strain & minor floaters. So it was a trade off to then have to wear non-prescription sunglasses during even slightly bright days (east coast likely not much of a problem, and certainly not for me here in London UK, but west coast and other sunny climes, more so).
...now if only they had something to fix my Tinnitus: tried sound generators from my specialist, but while they can work for a small percentage, they didn't work for me. :-/

snippet.textDisplay: I work in optics and I'd be very curious to know what your eyes have been corrected to. Being that you're a heavy device user, if you were corrected to have crystal clear 20/20 vision, around your mid 40's you'll eventually lose the ability to focus up close without needing glasses on. Did you intentionally get your eyes under corrected for far away, so the process of needing reading glasses was slowed down? I would love to know.
